DISTRIBUTIONS
A
NEW
METHOD
OF
CALCULATING
THE
BEHAVIOR
OF
TURBULENT
BOUNDARY
LAYERS
IN
ADVERSE
PRESSURE
DISTRIBUTIONS
IS
DEVELOPED
WHICH
PERMITS
DIRECT
DETERMINATION
OF
THE
VELOCITY
PROFILE
RATHER
THAN
THE
GROSS
INTEGRAL
PARAMETERS
NORMALLY
USED
TO
INFER
THE
GENERAL
CHARACTER
OF
THE
BOUNDARY
LAYER
THE
METHOD
OFFERS
THE
SIMPLICITY
OF
ALGEBRAIC
EQUATIONS
COUPLED
WITH
THE
USE
OF
CHARTS
RATHER
THAN
THE
LABORIOUS
SIMULTANEOUS
