OF
COUPLED
DIFFERENTIAL
EQUATIONS
REQUIRED
BY
EXISTING
METHODS
THE
METHOD
ALSO
AFFORDS
FOR
THE
FIRST
TIME
A
MEANS
OF
DETERMINING
THE
TOTAL
BOUNDARYLAYER
THICKNESS
THUS
ALLOWING
CALCULATION
OF
THE
ABSOLUTE
AS
WELL
AS
THE
NONDIMENSIONAL
VELOCITY
DISTRIBUTION
THE
VELOCITY
PROFILE
IS
CONSIDERED
TO
BE
COMPOSED
OF
TWO
REGIONSAN
INNER
REGION
WHICH
IS
DESCRIBED
BY
THE
LAW
OF
THE
WALL
AND
AN
OUTER
REGION
WHICH
IS
DESCRIBED
BY
A
FUNCTION
DEPICTING
THE
DEVIATION
FROM
THAT
LAW
THE
DEVIATION
FUNCTION
INVOLVES
TWO
PARAMETERS
WHICH
ARE
UNIQUELY
DEPENDENT
UPON
THE
SKINFRICTION
COEFFICIENT
AND
A
THIRD
PARAMETER
WHICH
FOR
PRACTICAL
